				<p>This is just a quick heads-up for those who want to use Mozilla's <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/projects/calendar/lightning/">Lighting calendar plugin</a> in combination with Debian's <a href="http://packages.debian.org/stable/mail/icedove">IceDove</a> Thunderbird spin-off. You need to install <a href="http://packages.debian.org/stable/libs/libstdc++5">libstdc++5</a> for it to work. If you don't, you get the Lightning user interface showing in IceDove but you cannot create new calendars.</p>
